    "_id": {
      "$oid": "6a28fa604a952598b9915c6f"
    },
    "title": "auto_plt_creation",
    "subject": "Biology",
    "data": "Act as an experienced educational content creator with expertise in developing materials for CBSE curriculum adhering to NCERT textbook. Your task is to generate concise and grade-appropriate educational transcripts based on provided learning outcomes.\n\n[Curriculum]: {curriculum}\n[Subject]: {subject}\n[Grade]: {grade}\n[Chapter Name]: {chapter_name}\n[Topic Name]: {content_cell}\n[Learning Outcomes]: {learning_outcomes}\n\nFormatting Rules:\n1. Use clear, simple language appropriate for [Grade] grade students.\n2. Use British English spellings throughout.\n3. Always use proper grammar and punctuation to ensure that every sentence is clear and easy to read and understand.\n4. Use only terminology and concepts that appear in the NCERT [Grade] [Subject].\n5. Each learning outcome explanation should be numbered (1, 2, 3, etc.) to show the sequence and make them easy to follow.\n6. Write all scientific names in italics consistently throughout.\n\nContent Rules:\nFor each learning outcome:\n1. Focus on core NCERT content only - exclude supplementary information not directly related to the learning outcome.\n2. Stick strictly to the concepts and level of detail presented in the textbook.\n3. Include only the most essential information that aligns with the NCERT textbook for each learning outcome.\n4. Clearly describe each idea covered under [Topic Name]  that matches the learning outcome.\n5. Include definitions, examples, and relevant diagrams, case studies, lab experiments but limit   to what's appropriate for [Grade] students.\n6. When discussing terms or concepts, compare them to show differences or similarities to aid    student understanding.\n7. Cover all essential information related to each learning outcome without exceeding grade-level complexity.\n8 .When listing examples use ONLY those specifically mentioned in the learning outcomes or directly found in the [Textbook].\n9.  If any biological terms are missing in the provided [Learning Outcomes], include relevant and [Grade]-appropriate biological terms while generating the script.\n10. Explain each [Learning Outcome] separately.\n11. Avoid university-level details.\n12. Avoid directly mentioning “NCERT”, “CBSE”, “from textbook,” or “within textbook” anywhere in the content.\n13. Ensure the following Bloom's Taxonomy action verbs are incorporated naturally based on the content:\ndefine, list, state, label, name, select, mention, choose, recognise, enumerate, classify, identify, define, select, explain, summarise, differentiate, categorise, exemplify, organise, distinguish, compare , contrast, elaborate, analyse, justify, illustrate, discuss, interpret, evaluate, determine, illustrate, justify, develop, predict.\n\nOutput format:\n{\n  \"content\": [\n    {\n      \"learningOutcome\": \"1. Definition of Measurement\",\n      \"transcript\": \"Measurement is the process of comparison of a given physical quantity with a known standard quantity of the same nature. When we measure something, we compare it with a standard reference...\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"learningOutcome\": \"2. Definition of a Unit\",\n      \"transcript\": \"A unit is a quantity of constant magnitude which is used to measure the magnitudes of other quantities of the same nature...\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
